gomodel:SYNGO_4517  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Neurocan inhibits Sema3F-induced spine retraction. Fig. 3 A shows apical dendrites and spines of mouse cortical neurons expressing EGFP in cultures treated with Fc or Sema3F-Fc. Pretreatment with 20 nM Neurocan prevented Sema3F-Fc induced spine collapse but did not affect spine density in Fc-treated control cultures. (B) Quantification of experiment in panel A, showing significant reduction in mean spine density upon Sema3F-Fc treatment by Neurocan. (C) NrCAM enhances Neurocan action as lower concentrations of Neurocan (8 nM) have a similar effect in preventing Sema3F-Fc induced spine collapse and did not affect spine density in Fc-treated control cultures.\n\nRelated to annotations ID 1889 and ID 2762. Experimental description: \"C57BL/6 WT mice (P18 and P80) were anesthetized and perfused transcardially with phosphate buffer...\" p.2" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4517" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

